Enum Constant Detail

OFF

public static final LQTracker.LQTrackerProfile OFF
Tracking is off.

ROUGH

public static final LQTracker.LQTrackerProfile ROUGH
The lowest useful data quality. Device is in a super battery-safe mode and location data may only be useful for large regions. Data is batched on the device, if the network drops out and later reconnects, no data is lost.

ADAPTIVE

public static final LQTracker.LQTrackerProfile ADAPTIVE
An adaptive data quality. Device may either be in a battery saving mode, or use more accurate location tracking when necessary to distinguish geofences. Data is batched on the device, then submitted to the server later. If the network drops out and later reconnects, no data is lost.

LOGGING

public static final LQTracker.LQTrackerProfile LOGGING
The highest quality data available. Data is batched on the device, then submitted to the server later. If the network drops out and later reconnects, no data is lost.

REAL_TIME

public static final LQTracker.LQTrackerProfile REAL_TIME
The highest quality, most real-time data available. Data is transmitted as soon as possible with low-latency networking. Old updates may be dropped as they are no longer relevant (after n minutes).
